JOHANNESBURG, October 29 (ANA) – A cyclist was critically injured when a car crashed into him along the R562 in Blue Hills, Midrand on Sunday morning, paramedics said. “It is understood that the driver of a vehicle lost control and crashed into the cyclist while he was sitting on a small embankment next to the road. The vehicle also collided with a nearby lamppost,” ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. The cyclist suffered multiple fractures and abdominal injuries. READ: Joburg cyclist seriously injured in taxi crash The ER24 Oneplan medical helicopter airlifted him to hospital. The driver was not injured. Local authorities attended the scene and would investigate, Vermaak said. African News Agency